An urgent search has been launched for twin girls, 11, who disappeared from their home on Tuesday night. Gracie and Millie Bennett were reported missing at around 8.30pm after being last seen at their family’s house in Mountsorrel, Leicestershire. Their family and police are concerned for them and are asking for the public’s help to find them. They are both are white, 4ft 8ins tall and of a slim build, with straight, dark brown hair below their shoulders. Gracie was wearing a navy blue hoody with the initials ‘MB’ on the chest. She also had blue jeans and white Puma trainers on. Millie was wearing wearing a black Nike Tec jumper, black jeans and white high-topped Nike trainers when she went missing. One of the girls is also carrying a cream-coloured backpack, while the other may have a navy backpack with white spots. Anyone with information is urged to come forward to Leicestershire Police. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.